It has one annotated transcript and one polypeptide. Gene sequence location is 2L:9932272..9933163. Its molecular function is described by: structural constituent of chitin-based larval cuticle. It is involved in the biological process described with: chitin-based cuticle development. 4 alleles are reported. The phenotypes of these alleles manifest in: larval neuroblast; ganglion mother cell; mesonotum; trichogen cell. The phenotypic classes of alleles include: lethal; some die during P-stage; increased mortality during development; phenotype. Summary of modENCODE Temporal Expression Profile:  Temporal profile ranges from a peak of extremely high expression to a trough of no expression detected.  Peak expression observed during late pupal stages.
